claim.claim-text:
1. A apparatus for interfacing a socket to a testing apparatus which comprises: 
a base member; 
a first electrically conductive contact member being removably attachable to the base member; 
the first contact member having a first portion thereof sized and shaped to engage an electrical contact on the testing apparatus and a second portion thereof sized and shaped to engage a second contact member; 
a second contact member having a first portion thereof sized and shaped to engage the second portion of the first contact member; and 
the second contact member being removably and electrically connectable to the socket.

9. A system for testing an electronic device which comprises: 
a testing apparatus including a test fixture for interfacing with electronic devices to be tested; 
a base member; 
a first electrically conductive contact member being removably attachable to the base member; 
the first contact member having a first portion thereof sized and shaped to engage an electrical contact on the test fixture and a second portion thereof sized and shaped to engage a second contact member; 
a second contact member having a first portion thereof sized and shaped to engage the second portion of the first contact member; and 
the second contact member being removably and electrically connectable to the socket.

17. A method for interfacing a relatively small number of electrical devices to be tested with a high volume testing device comprising the acts of: 
attaching a first set of contacts to the testing device; 
removably fixing a second set of contacts in contact with the first set of contacts; 
attaching a removable electrical socket to the second set of contacts; and 
placing a device to be tested within the socket.
